---
description: Internal navigation must render a real <a> element for cmd/middle/right-click "Open in new tab" to work
alwaysApply: true
---

## Internal links must be real anchors

Every navigation to another route in this app MUST produce a real `<a>` element in the DOM so that:
- right-click → "Open in new tab" works
- cmd/ctrl+click opens in a new tab
- middle-click opens in a new tab

### Patterns

**Inline links** — always use `<NuxtLink>`:
```vue
<NuxtLink to="/some/path">Label</NuxtLink>
```

**Button-styled CTAs that only navigate** — use `<Button as="NuxtLink" :to="...">`:
```vue
<Button as="NuxtLink" to="/tiers" label="View plans" rounded />
<Button as="NuxtLink" to="/admin" severity="secondary" aria-label="Back">
  <template #icon><Icon name="tabler:chevron-left" /></template>
</Button>
```

**Full-row / full-card click targets that contain inner links or buttons** — use the **background NuxtLink overlay** pattern (see `.cursor/skills/clickable-rows/SKILL.md`):
```vue
<div class="relative cursor-pointer hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-zinc-900"
     role="link" tabindex="0"
     @click="onRowClick(href, $event)"
     @auxclick="onRowAuxClick(href, $event)"
     @keydown.enter.prevent="navigateTo(href)"
     @keydown.space.prevent="navigateTo(href)"
>
  <NuxtLink :to="href" class="absolute inset-0 z-[1]" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="true" />
  <div class="relative z-[2]"><!-- content --></div>
</div>
```

### What stays as `<Button @click>` (exceptions)

Buttons whose primary purpose is **mutating state** (and may navigate as a side-effect) stay as regular buttons:
- "Accept invite", "Decline", "Follow back", "Nudge back" — these POST to the API first
- Anything that shows a confirmation dialog before navigating
- PrimeVue MenuItem `command:` callbacks (popup menu items use `command`, not `href`)

### Never do these

```vue
<!-- ❌ not a real <a> — right-click won't offer "Open in new tab" -->
<Button @click="navigateTo('/some/path')" label="Go" />

<!-- ❌ div role="link" is accessible but not a native anchor -->
<NuxtLink custom v-slot="{ navigate }" to="/path">
  <div role="link" @click="navigate($event)">...</div>
</NuxtLink>

<!-- ❌ @click on non-anchor for primary navigation -->
<tr @click="navigateTo('/path')">...</tr>
```
